First of all, thank you very much for the challenge!  I might not be
eligible for the actual contest (I'm not a British resident), but I
had a lot of fun fighting with this.

The two lists contain movie actors and actresses in (plaintext-wise)
alphabetical order:

            ---MEN---                            ---WOMEN---
Humphrey Bogart   (KCRVKXHL EUJDXZ)   Lauren Bacall       (TVFAMI WVYVTT)
Richard Burton     (WKNJVWL GSWOXU)   Kim Basinger         (KHP FNWHQBEV)
Sean Connery         (HYUE WREEYCS)   Ingrid Bergman     (MTJXMG EHXJRDT)
Tony Curtis           (QFDX ORNQTP)   Honor Blackman     (ORERC VIUWFNUE)
Albert Finney       (VTWMAC UEIIML)   Marlene Dietrich (AIKUSBS EHSMKHNR)
Harrison Ford       (OFIIPTYX LYIJ)   Kirsten Dunst       (UQPIDJX HEXID)
Alec Guinness       (ZGRT BPDIIRNN)   Carrie Fisher       (TZMMDR WDNCRM)
Rex Harrison         (XCT GSXXJYUQ)   Jodie Foster         (ECWHX YCMBXA)
Anthony Hopkins   (RNBTCNP TCOSHNM)   Judy Garland         (LRNU FHZOHVN)
John Hurt               (XIVL VFBD)   Linda Hamilton     (YVTLG UGZVYNHT)
Charles Laughton (NRIKUSL UIQORMDB)   Audrey Hepburn     (YAERFI KFXBARV)
Jack Lemmon           (UFIV WKXXZY)   Katharine Hepburn
Tobey Maguire       (DYFJN WCLEQPJ)                   (OUGEUDLRZ EZBVJDR)
Ewan McGregor       (LVZD CONKLNFK)   Scarlett Johansson
Bill Murray           (PZSS TEBBMJ)                  (CQMBSVDD LNYMICCNI)
Peter O'Toole       (BZGZD A'GAANZ)   Nicole Kidman       (DGOFBL AGUCZD)
Gregory Peck         (JRFJWRI XFCS)   Shirley MacLaine (AQSEWKC XFIWFSYK)
Mickey Rooney       (QJAMDU ZWWVDU)   Kelly McGillis     (RKUUC VHMPUUPT)
Arnold Schwarzenegger                 Marilyn Monroe     (CZNTBXD CFDNFE)
            (GMTHYL IKUBGMFPTPSSPM)   Margaret Rutherford
Kevin Spacey         (KEZHQ WSNIEC)                 (OSXFSXCZ XBZGCXDUXA)
                                      Elizabeth Taylor (BQKDVGBOJ OVIQXW)
                                      Sigourney Weaver (CWUIFBLSK HSOGSB)

Each of the names is encrypted using a simple substitution cipher.
The ciphertext alphabet order for each cipher is formed, starting from
the title of a movie, by removing duplicate letters, adding the unused
letters in order, and shifting the alphabet (as in the June puzzle).

The connection between the women and the men is that one actor and one
actress share each cipher.  The shared cipher is always based on the
title of a movie that both people acted in.  Note, however, that the
connection really is ciphers rather than movies: in a few cases, a
third person from the lists acted in one of the movies, but they will
get encrypted with a cipher from some other movie they acted in.

Here is a list of all the actor/actress pairs, ciphertext alphabets
used to encrypt them, and the movies used for cipher keys:

Mickey Rooney                         Judy Garland
           HBANDCFGJLMOQVWXYZSTRIKEUP
           Strike Up the Band  (1940)

